A collection of [mostly rubyish] utilities.  See the different folders for more complete descriptions.

=================

unique_require: allows Ruby 1.8.x to only require a file once, regardless of the different path strings used to require a file.

micro_pause: a ruby shoes app that pops up and reminds you to take carpal tunnel breaks.

drive_speed_test: a ruby script to test how fast a hard drive runs.  Creates a large file then many files, outputes how long it took [extremely simple drive speed test].

old-useful. Contains many of the [somewhat useful] files from http://code.google.com/p/ruby-roger-useful-functions/

Note: some older useful ruby/rails utilities may also be found at http://code.google.com/p/ruby-roger-useful-functions [english like queries, table syncer, named parameters]
